-- Swiss Stocks Decline; SMI Retreats 0.2 Percent as Credit Suisse Retreats
-- Sarah Jones
-- 2010-07-22T08:19:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/swiss-stocks-decline-smi-retreats-0-2-percent-as-credit-suisse-retreats.html

          
          
             Swiss stocks retreated, led by
declines in Credit Suisse Group AG and Syngenta AG.  
 The benchmark Swiss Market Index slipped 0.2 percent to
6,112.53 at 10:18 a.m. in Zurich. The gauge earlier pared losses
as shares of ABB Ltd. and Lonza Group AG advanced.  
          
          


  


        